# Palmetto Partnership Quoting Tool

*Design Requirements Document*

**Version 1.3 | January 2026**

---

## Summary

### Goal

Enable solar sales representatives from Palmetto partner organizations to generate HVAC quotes for homeowners in real-time during in-home consultations, facilitating a seamless cross-sell opportunity that drives value for both the solar installation and HVAC upgrade sale.

### Scope

This design covers Phase 1 (Sales) of the Palmetto partnership user journey, specifically:

- User authentication and team management
- Address entry and digital twin generation
- Housing details confirmation
- Energy usage visualization and editing
- Quote customization (commission, equipment, notes)
- Product selection and comparison
- Checkout flow (payment method, scheduling, quote sharing)
- Deposit collection with social proof
- Homeowner-facing project status view
- Change order management

### Out of Scope

- Phase 2: Install operations (handled by Sibi)
- Phase 3: Payment processing and reconciliation (handled by Tetra backend)
- Material ordering workflow (handled by Sibi)
- Palmetto financing application integration (external system)

---

## Personas

### Primary: Solar Sales Representative

*"Alex"* - Field sales professional working for a Palmetto partner solar installation company.

**Key characteristics:**

- In-home with homeowners during solar consultations
- Identifies HVAC cross-sell opportunities through conversation
- Needs to generate quotes quickly to maintain sales momentum
- Motivated by commission on HVAC sales
- May not have deep HVAC technical knowledge
- Works primarily on tablet or laptop in the field

**Pain points:**

- Complex quoting tools lose homeowner engagement
- Uncertain about equipment sizing and pricing
- Needs real-time availability and pricing information
- Wants to close deals in one visit

### Secondary: Sales Manager

*"Jordan"* - Team lead responsible for managing solar sales reps and commission structures.

**Key characteristics:**

- Manages team of 5-20 sales representatives
- Sets default commission rates for the team
- Needs visibility into team activity and pipeline
- Onboards new sales reps to the platform

### Tertiary: Homeowner

*"Pat"* - Homeowner considering both solar and HVAC upgrades.

**Key characteristics:**

- Originally interested in solar installation
- Open to learning about complementary home upgrades
- Wants to understand total cost and financing options
- May need to review proposal after the sales visit
- Expects visibility into project status after purchase

---

## Jobs to be Done

| Job Category | Job Statement |
|--------------|---------------|
| Quote Generation | When I identify an HVAC opportunity, I want to quickly generate an accurate quote so I can close the deal while the homeowner is engaged. |
| Equipment Selection | When I need to recommend HVAC equipment, I want to see only available options with real-time pricing so I can confidently present options to the homeowner. |
| Commission Management | When I need to adjust pricing for a deal, I want to easily modify my commission so I can maintain competitiveness while protecting my earnings. |
| Customer Communication | When a homeowner wants to review later, I want to send them the quote via email or text so they can make an informed decision at their convenience. |
| Deal Closing | When the homeowner is ready to proceed, I want to collect payment method, deposit, and schedule installation so I can complete the sale in one visit. |
| Team Management | When I onboard new sales reps, I want to easily add them to the system with appropriate permissions so they can start selling immediately. |
| Change Orders | When install requirements change, I want to communicate the price impact to the homeowner and get approval so the project can continue without delays. |

---

## Primary Apps

### Existing Apps Used

| App | Role in This Design |
|-----|---------------------|
| Quoting Tool | Core application adapted for solar sales rep use. Provides address entry, digital twin, equipment selection, and quote generation. |
| Homeowner Dashboard | Extended to serve as the post-sale Success Page, showing project status and timeline to homeowners. |

### New Functionality Required

| Feature | Justification | Primary Purpose |
|---------|---------------|-----------------|
| User Management Module | Existing quoting tool lacks team management. Solar orgs need to manage their own sales reps. | Add/remove users, set commission defaults, manage permissions |
| Customizations Screen | Existing tool lacks in-flow customization. Sales reps need to adjust quotes without leaving the flow. | Commission adjustment, equipment sizing, condenser addition, installer notes |
| Scheduling Integration | Current quoting tool does not include install scheduling. Required to close deals in one visit. | Display available install windows, capture preferred time |
| Change Order Screen | No existing mechanism for post-sale modifications. Critical for handling install-day discoveries. | Display change details, get approval, capture additional payment method |

---

## Primary Screens

The following screens comprise the Palmetto Quoting Tool experience:

1. **Login** â€” Authentication for sales representatives
2. **User Management** â€” Team member and commission administration
3. **Address Entry** â€” Property identification and digital twin generation
4. **Housing Details** â€” Confirmation and editing of property characteristics
5. **Energy Usage** â€” Visualization and adjustment of energy consumption data
6. **Customizations** â€” Quote adjustments for commission, equipment, and installer notes
7. **Product Listing** â€” Equipment options comparison and selection
8. **Product Details** â€” Detailed equipment specifications and payback analysis
9. **Summary & Checkout** â€” Final review, payment method, scheduling, and quote sharing
10. **Deposit** â€” Payment collection with social proof
11. **Success** â€” Homeowner-facing project status after sale
12. **Change Order** â€” Post-sale modification approval

