## 12. Change Order

### Goal

Enable homeowners to review and approve change orders that arise during installation, presenting change items in a familiar visual format consistent with the add-on selection experience while clearly communicating the cost impact.

### Journey

**Entry:**
- Success page notification/alert when change order requires approval
- Direct link from change order email/SMS notification
- Sales rep sharing screen with homeowner during follow-up call

**Steps:**
1. System displays change order header with reason from installer
2. Homeowner reviews list of change items grouped by category (Additions, Modifications, Removals)
3. Homeowner reviews price summary showing original total, change amount, and new total
4. If additional payment required, homeowner selects payment method for the change amount
5. Homeowner approves or declines the change order
6. If approved with payment required, system processes payment for difference

**Exit:**
- Approved â†’ Success page (updated project status)
- Declined â†’ Job cancelled or escalation to support (based on installer action)
- Contact support action â†’ External support channel
- Share action â†’ Email/SMS sent with change order link

### Functionality

| Functionality | Description |
|---------------|-------------|
| Display change order header | Show change order title with reason provided by Sibi/installer (e.g., "Electrical panel upgrade needed based on site inspection") |
| Display change items by category | Group items into categories: Additions (new items), Modifications (changed specifications), Removals (items no longer needed/credits) |
| Display item details | For each change item: icon/image (contextual to item type), title, price impact (+$X or -$X), description explaining the change |
| Display price summary | Show Original Total, Change Order Amount (+/-), and New Total with monthly payment format where applicable |
| Payment method selection | For change orders with price increase: display payment method options (Cash, Loan, Lease) for the change amount only |
| Route to financing | If Loan or Lease selected for change amount, initiate Palmetto financing check for the difference amount |
| Approve change order | Confirm acceptance, process payment if required, update job record, notify Sibi |
| Decline change order | Reject changes, trigger notification to sales rep and Sibi for next steps (may result in job cancellation) |
| Contact support | Provide support contact options for questions about the change order |
| Share change order | Send change order details via email or SMS for review by other decision-makers |

### Components

*Reference: engineering/design-system.md*

| Functionality | Recommended Components |
|---------------|------------------------|
| Change order header | SectionHeader with StatusTag (warning variant) indicating pending approval status |
| Change item display | Item cards following add-on pattern: icon/image (left), title + description (center), price (right). Use contextual icons: plus for additions, swap/exchange for modifications, minus for removals/credits |
| Category grouping | Bold section headers as in add-ons screen (e.g., "Additions", "Modifications", "Credits") |
| Price summary | LineItemList component showing Original Total, Change Amount, New Total. Display monthly payment format (+$X /mo) consistent with add-ons pattern |
| Payment method selection | Selectable cards (following same pattern as Summary & Checkout screen) |
| Payment processing | PaymentForm component for collecting payment on price increases |
| Approve action | Button (primary) in StickyFooter - "Approve Changes" |
| Decline action | Button (destructive variant) - "Decline Changes" |
| Support contact | ContactInfoItem or action link |
| Share action | Secondary action for email/SMS sharing |

### Design Pattern Reference

The Change Order screen adapts the add-on selection pattern with the following key differences:

| Add-on Pattern Element | Change Order Adaptation |
|------------------------|-------------------------|
| Selectable checkboxes on each item | No checkboxes - change order items are presented as a package to approve or decline together |
| Individual item selection | All items displayed as informational - homeowner reviews but does not select individual items |
| Single primary CTA ("Continue") | Two CTAs: Approve (primary) and Decline (destructive) |
| Optional add-on pricing | Mandatory change order pricing - homeowner must address before installation continues |
| Product images | Contextual icons indicating change type (plus, swap, minus) with optional product image where relevant |
| Helper text below CTA | Helper text with support contact option: "Questions? Contact support" or "Not sure? Talk to your sales rep" |

### User Flow Alignment

This screen supports the Change Order flow from Phase 2 (Install) of the Palmetto user journey:

| Journey Node | Screen Functionality |
|--------------|---------------------|
| CO_UpdateQuote (Send Message with Change Order Details) | Triggers creation of this screen content with items and pricing |
| CO_UpdateJob (Update the Job) | System creates change order record in Tetra |
| CO_NotifySalesRep (Notify the Sales Rep) | Sales rep receives notification, may share screen with HO |
| CO_SalesFollowUp (Sales Follow Up) | Entry point - sales rep guides HO to review change order |
| Dec_HOApproved (HO Approved?) | Approve/Decline actions determine exit path |
| Dec_COPaymentMethod (Change Order Payment Method?) | Payment method selection functionality |
| CO_UpdateJobRecord (Update Job Record) | Triggered on approval, updates Tetra and Sibi |

### Edge Cases

| Scenario | Expected Behavior |
|----------|-------------------|
| Change order reduces total price | Display credit amount with minus icon, no payment required. Price summary shows negative change amount. Inform homeowner of credit applied to final invoice. |
| Change order has no price impact | Display scope changes without price column. Hide payment method selection. Show "No additional payment required" message. |
| Multiple items in change order | Group items by category (Additions, Modifications, Credits). Display scrollable list if items exceed viewport. |
| Single item change order | Display single item card without category header if only one category represented. |
| Mix of additions and removals | Show net price impact in summary. Display items in logical category order: Additions first, then Modifications, then Removals/Credits. |
| Financing selected but denied | Display denial message, offer alternative payment options (cash, different financing product). |
| Financing application times out | Show timeout message with retry option and cash payment alternative. |
| Change order exceeds original financing limit | Route to Palmetto for full re-qualification if loan/lease cannot cover increase. [CLARIFICATION NEEDED: Palmetto financing limit rules] |
| Homeowner wants to discuss before deciding | Provide contact support action prominently. Allow sharing change order via email/SMS for review with family or other decision-makers. |
| Change order expires | [CLARIFICATION NEEDED: Is there a time limit on change order approval? Define behavior if expired.] |
| Partial approval requested | V1: Not supported - change order is all-or-nothing. Display message explaining homeowner must accept or decline entire change order. Contact support for custom arrangements. |
| Original payment was cash, change order uses financing | Allow different payment method for change order amount. Clearly indicate this applies only to the additional amount. |

### Error States

| Error Condition | User Message | Recovery Action |
|-----------------|--------------|-----------------|
| Change order already processed | This change order has already been processed. See your project status for the latest details. | Link to Success page with updated status |
| Change order cancelled by installer | This change order is no longer valid. The installer has cancelled the request. Please contact support if you have questions. | Display support contact, link to Success page |
| Payment for change order failed | Payment could not be processed. Please check your card details or try a different payment method. | Clear payment form, allow retry with same or different card |
| Financing denied for change order | The financing application for the additional amount was not approved. You can still proceed with a cash payment for the difference. | Show cash payment option, offer contact support |
| Financing application timeout | We're having trouble processing your financing application. Please try again or choose a different payment option. | Show retry button, show cash alternative |
| Network error during approval | We couldn't process your approval. Your payment has not been charged. Please check your connection and try again. | Show retry action |
| Change order data failed to load | We couldn't load the change order details. Please try again or contact support. | Retry action, support contact link |
| Job not found | We couldn't find this project. Please check your confirmation email or contact support for assistance. | Support contact only |
| Session expired during review | Your session has expired. Please log in again to continue reviewing this change order. | Link to login, preserve change order reference for return |

